      "content": "The most common technical and process-driven reasons for \"phantom inventory\" (where the system shows stock that is physically missing) usually stem from **data synchronization delays**, **incorrect bin assignments**, or **system configuration errors**.\n\nHere are the specific technical and process causes to investigate:\n\n1.  **Unposted Goods Receipts or Adjustments:**\n    Sometimes, a goods receipt is entered into the system, but the physical movement hasn't happened yet, or an adjustment (like a return to vendor) was logged but the item wasn't physically moved back to the main stock area. If the system thinks the item is in the warehouse but it's actually on a truck or in a quarantine zone, it creates a phantom count.\n\n2.  **Bin Assignment Drift (The \"Wrong Bin\" Issue):**\n    This is a very common technical cause. If an item is moved to a new location but the system's last known location (the \"home\" bin) hasn't been updated, the system will still show the item in the old bin. When you physically count the old bin, you find nothing, but the system says it's there. This often happens if staff use manual \"move\" commands without scanning the \"out",
